text: I used to have really bad back pain with a strong muscle twinge near my spine from sitting at my PC all day. I fixed it by buying an adjustable bed frame with a memory foam mattress (Nectar sleep). I took my OLED TV, set it on a table at the foot of my bed and bought a lap keyboard/mouse pad combo (Corsair) and now if I have to use the computer for a long time, I just raise my bed and use my PC like that and my back issues went away within a week. This keeps your back straight at all times, no compression on your spine and better blood circulation. Hell, sometimes I never even have to get out of bed. Wake up, raise my bed and use my pc instantly.
